  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:42 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC stayed a clean leader-long after the short side cleared\n\n**Task:** Run a fresh HL leaderboard scan after the 22:07 UTC BTC short-side clearing and test whether leader longs started distributing into strength.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output moved to **BTC 7L/0S**, **ETH 3L/5S**, **SOL 4L/4S**.\n- By notional, the copy book is now:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$13.17M** vs shorts **$0.00M** \u2192 net **+$13.17M long**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.12M** vs shorts **$38.64M** \u2192 net **-$38.52M short**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.21M** vs shorts **$11.51M** \u2192 net **-$11.30M short**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.62M** vs shorts **$11.89M** \u2192 net **-$10.26M short**\n- BTC improved from **6L/1S** to **7L/0S** because the tiny remaining BTC short from `beatmaker1@proton.me` flipped back to **BTC LONG $0.15M**.\n- No tracked top-20 BTC shorts remain.\n- BTC long notional stayed almost unchanged: **$13.28M -> $13.17M**.\n- The top BTC long block did **not** distribute:\n  - **anon-0xfc66:** still **BTC LONG $5.63M**\n  - **anon-0xecb6:** **$4.90M -> $4.93M**\n  - **anon-0x57dd:** **$2.22M -> $2.16M** (small trim only)\n- ETH count softened, but notional is still deeply short: **$38.64M short vs $0.12M long**.\n- SOL count neutralized to **4L/4S**, but size is still bearish: **$11.51M short vs $0.21M long**.\n- HYPE stayed bearish by size at **-$10.26M net short**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-clean-long-holds-sol-count-neutral-2026-05-02-2242.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC's clean bullish read survived the immediate follow-up. That matters because the next failure mode would have been top-long distribution after the bear side disappeared. Instead, the big three BTC longs held basically steady and the remaining BTC sh